1. k version => to get cluster verison 
2. k get node => to get info about the cluster nodes
3. k get node -o wide => to get more info about the cluster nodes
4. k get pod => to get info about cluster pods
5. k get pod -o wide => to get more info about cluster pods
6. k run <podname> --image <imagename> => to run a pod
7. k describe pod <podname> => to get all info about a specific pod
8. k delete pod <podname> => to delete a pod
9. k run <podname> --image <imagename> --dry-run=client -o yaml > mypod.yml => to create a yaml file for the pod


ReplicaSet
1. k get rs => to get info about replicasets
2. k edit rs <rsname> => to edit a replicaset
3. k delete rs <rsname> => to delete a rs
4. k scale rs <rsname> --replicas <numberofpods> => to scale a replicaset
5. k api-resources => to get the api version and kind of k8s resources
6. Note matchlables must be equal to labes in the template
7. k create -f <filename>  => create a resource
8. k delete -f <filename>  => delete a resource
9. k apply -f <filename>   => edit a resource ( or create it ) 


Deployment
1. k create deployment <deployname> --image <imagename> => to create a deployment
2. k create deployment <deployname> --image <imagename> --dry-run=client -o yaml > mydeply.yml => to create a yaml file for the deployment
3. k get deploy => to get info about the deploy
4. k describe deploy <deployname> => to get all info about a specific deployment
5. k edit deploy <deployname> => to edit deploy


